Yatra: A journey towards consciousness
____________________

Our story begins with the dawn of 11th century, when Emperor Nayapala is ruling the rich and peaceful lands of Vanga. But this peace doesn't sustain long the flag of war unfurls, King Lakshmikarna of the Kalachuri dynasty attacks Vanga, spreading anarchy all around.
In the mean time The great monk, Atish Dipankara Srijjana appears as a ray hope, he puts an end to the war by establishing the word of peace and harmony between the two emperors.
After the great war, around 1040 AD, the great Atisha was invited by Emperor Jnanaprabha to spread Buddhism in his kingdom Tibet. Through the snow-capped, paths of the silk route the great monk travelled carrying his mystic offerings of profound enlightenment, 'The Saptagunas'.
The metaphorical Saptagunas were the reflections of Atisha's ownself and his own qualities of Immortality, Prosperity, Wisdom, Valour, Fearlessness, Fortune and Love.
As the great monk reached Tibet, he was welcomed by Emperor Jnanaprabha in a great celebratory manner and was venerated with sumptuous offerings to pay homage to the great monk, while the air fills with chants praising the heavenly being.

*আলো ছায়া*
*Aalo Chaya*
Bridal trousseau 2022
Anirban Mondal  x Agnik Kolkata 
a film by Anjanava Mitra

এক অন্য রূপ কথার গল্প, যেখানে কাজল  কালো রাজকন্যার দীর্ঘ অপেক্ষার অবসান হয়, ঘোড়ায় চড়ে, সুখ-সম্মান-স্বীকৃতি নিয়ে আসে তার স্বপ্নে দেখা এক রাজপুত্তুর. আলোর মায়া আলিঙ্গন করে ছায়ার সৌন্দর্য, দুয়ে মিলে হয়ে ওঠে একে ওপরের অভিন্ন অঙ্গ, 'আলো - ছায়া'.

A tale quite different from all other, where the long lost wish of the dark-eyed princess is fulfilled as the prince in his dream arrives with all the happiness, love and acceptance. The trance of Aalo entraps the radiant Chhaya as they get entwined in one, 'Aalo-Chhaya'.

A film by @anjanavaphotos

Style is a way to define your character without having to speak

The entire video was shot on Canon's R6 Mark II camera body with Canon RF STM 35mm F1.8 Macro and Canon RF 85mm F2.0 Macro lenses. All these shots are used in this reel are taken handheld, and no gimble and stabilizer was used. The in body motion stabilization is amazing for that price range of camera bodies and Canon's C LoG unfolds the post process capabilities too.
